events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Chris Davis raced 100-plus yards with a missed field-goal attempt for a touchdown on the final play to lift No. 4 Auburn to a 34-28 victory over No. 1 Alabama on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Auburn stuns Alabama on FG return

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Jameis Winston threw three touchdown passes to Kelvin Benjamin, and No. 2 Florida State moved a step closer to playing for the national championship with a 37-7 victory against rival Florida on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: FSU rolls to ACC title game

events.name: Clemson Tigers at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Connor Shaw threw for one touchdown and rushed for another as No. 10 South Carolina won its record fifth straight over No. 6 Clemson with 31-17 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: South Carolina again topples Clemson

events.name: Notre Dame Fighting Irish at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Wayne Lyons intercepted two passes from Tommy Rees late in the fourth quarter, and No. 8 Stanford held off No. 25 Notre Dame 27-20 on Saturday night in the regular-season finale for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford stymies Notre Dame

events.name: Baylor Bears at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Bryce Petty threw for two touchdowns and ran for another, Baylor returned two interceptions for scores and the No. 9 Bears hung on for a 41-38 victory over TCU on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 9 Baylor maintains BCS hopes

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Jeremy Langford ran for 134 yards and a touchdown, and No. 11 Michigan State wrapped up an unbeaten regular season in Big Ten play with a 14-3 victory over Minnesota on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spartans complete perfect Big Ten season

events.name: Arizona Wildcats at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.description: D.J. Foster ran for 124 yards and two touchdowns, and No. 12 Arizona State dismantled rival Arizona 58-21 Saturday night to earn home-field advantage in next week's Pac-12 championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: ASU rips Arizona; will host Pac-12 title game

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Christian Hackenberg threw for 339 yards and four touchdowns, and Penn State pounced on a slew of blunders before holding off a late rally to upset No. 14 Wisconsin 31-24 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn St. shocks Badgers

events.name: UCLA Bruins at USC Trojans

headlines.description: Brett Hundley passed for 208 yards and rushed for two touchdowns, leading No. 22 UCLA past No. 23 Southern California 35-14 Saturday night and winning the crosstown showdown for the second straight season.
headlines.shortLinkText: UCLA makes it 2 in row vs. USC
